Issues.Body:
### Background and motivation

I have a complex application which has multiple forms and each form runs in a indenpendent STA thread due to heavy UI renderer job, this makes it has to call Invoke() to access other forms' handles. However, Control's Handle only needs to ensure thread safety during creation in reality, is it possible that we only check thread safety when the handle is not created, so that we can safety and efficiently get Control's Handle in other thread after Handle created.
I know Control.Handle is a very basic and widely used member, so I hope we can carefully discuss it.

### API Proposal

```csharp
    public IntPtr Handle
    {
        get
        {
            if (CheckForIllegalCrossThreadCalls && !t_inCrossThreadSafeCall && InvokeRequired)
            {
                throw new InvalidOperationException(string.Format(SR.IllegalCrossThreadCall, Name));
            }

            if (!IsHandleCreated)
            {
                CreateHandle();
            }

            return HandleInternal;
        }
    }
```
Changes to be:
``` csharp
    public IntPtr Handle
    {
        get
        {
            if (!IsHandleCreated)
            {
                if (CheckForIllegalCrossThreadCalls && !t_inCrossThreadSafeCall && InvokeRequired)
                {
                    throw new InvalidOperationException(string.Format(SR.IllegalCrossThreadCall, Name));
                }

                CreateHandle();
            }

            return HandleInternal;
        }
    }
```


### API Usage

```csharp
Task.Factory.StartNew(()=> _ = control.Handle);
```


